## Verify

Verify the bundle's integrity before running any installer.

**Linux:**
```bash
sha256sum -c {{BUNDLE_NAME}}-{{VERSION}}.tar.gz.sha256
```

**macOS** (`shasum` ships with Xcode Command Line Tools; `sha256sum` is absent by default):
```bash
shasum -a 256 -c {{BUNDLE_NAME}}-{{VERSION}}.tar.gz.sha256
```

Both commands print `{{BUNDLE_NAME}}-{{VERSION}}.tar.gz: OK` on success and exit non-zero on mismatch.

## Extract

```bash
tar -xzf {{BUNDLE_NAME}}-{{VERSION}}.tar.gz
```

## Install (macOS/Linux)

> **Security notice:** `install.sh` installs the bundle contents into your repo — selected
> `.claude/` artifacts PLUS any packed top-level files (e.g. `README.md`, `CLAUDE.md`).
> Each skill in the bundle may also ship its own `install.sh` hook (sets up a venv, etc.).
> These per-skill hooks execute on your machine and run only when you pass `RUN_HOOKS=1`.
> **Review `install.sh` and each `.claude/skills/*/install.sh` before running.**

```bash
cd {{BUNDLE_NAME}}-{{VERSION}}/ && bash install.sh
```

To also run per-skill setup hooks (e.g. venv creation):
```bash
cd {{BUNDLE_NAME}}-{{VERSION}}/ && RUN_HOOKS=1 bash install.sh
```

Optional (opt-in, off by default): enable the product-spec memory hook with `bash .claude/skills/product-spec/install.sh --memory-hook`.

## Install (Windows)

> **Security notice:** Same as above — `install.ps1` installs the bundle contents into your repo.
> Review `install.ps1` and each `.claude/skills/*/install.ps1` before running.
> Per-skill hooks run only when you pass `-RunHooks`.

```powershell
cd {{BUNDLE_NAME}}-{{VERSION}}\
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\install.ps1
```

To also run per-skill setup hooks:
```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\install.ps1 -RunHooks
```

## What gets installed

{{FILE_COUNT}} files, {{TOTAL_SIZE}} into your repo. Files under `.claude/` go
into the matching path in your repo; any top-level files (e.g. `README.md`,
`CLAUDE.md`) that were included in the bundle are installed at your repo root.
See `MANIFEST.json` for the full list with per-file SHA256.

## Gitignore

The installer automatically adds `.claude/telemetry/` to your `.gitignore` (idempotent — safe
to run multiple times). The telemetry skill writes local usage data to that directory; it should
not be committed to source control.

## Troubleshooting

If a skill fails to load, verify that Claude Code can find `.claude/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`
in your repo root. Re-run `bash install.sh` (or `install.ps1`) to repair missing files, or
set `FORCE_OVERWRITE=1` to replace them. For skill-specific setup (e.g. Python venv), re-run
with `RUN_HOOKS=1`.

## Uninstall

```bash
# Remove an installed skill
rm -rf .claude/skills/<installed-skill>/

# Or restore from your backup taken at install time (FORCE_OVERWRITE creates timestamped backups)
```
